BT /F2 22 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 780 Tm (Next Word Prediction Project Guide) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 741 Tm (1. Project Introduction) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 708 Tm (This project is a full-stack next word prediction system. Its goal is to help users) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 693 Tm (type faster by suggesting the most likely next words based on the text they have) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 678 Tm (already entered.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 652 Tm (The project contains three main parts:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 626 Tm (- a frontend where the user types text and sees suggestions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 608 Tm (- a backend API that receives the text and returns predictions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 590 Tm (- a machine learning training pipeline that prepares and trains the LSTM model) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 564 Tm (This guide explains the project from start to end in simple language.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 538 Tm (2. Main Idea Of The Project) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 505 Tm (The idea is very simple:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 479 Tm (1. The user types a few words.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 461 Tm (2. The frontend sends that text to the backend.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 443 Tm (3. The backend checks whether a trained LSTM model is available.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 425 Tm (4. If the model is available, it predicts the top next words.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 407 Tm (5. If the model is not available, the backend uses the fallback predictor.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 389 Tm (6. The frontend shows the suggestions as buttons.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 371 Tm (7. When the user clicks one, it gets added to the sentence and new suggestions are) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 356 Tm (generated.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 330 Tm (So the project behaves like a small smart keyboard suggestion system.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 304 Tm (3. Project Flow From Start To End) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 271 Tm (The complete flow is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 245 Tm (- dataset text is stored in the data folder) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 227 Tm (- the training script reads the dataset) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 209 Tm (- the text is cleaned and tokenized) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 191 Tm (- sequences are created for next-word learning) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 173 Tm (- the LSTM model is trained) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 155 Tm (- the tokenizer and trained model are saved in artifacts) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 137 Tm (- the Flask backend loads those artifacts during runtime) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 119 Tm (- the frontend sends user text to the backend API) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 101 Tm (- the backend returns prediction results in JSON) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 83 Tm (- the frontend renders those words on the screen) Tj ET
endstream
