BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 498 Tm (- `training/train_lstm.py`) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 472 Tm (Tokenizer) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 443 Tm (Why it is used:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 417 Tm (- a machine learning model cannot understand raw words directly) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 399 Tm (- words must be converted into numeric IDs) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 373 Tm (How it works here:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 347 Tm (- builds a vocabulary from the dataset) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 329 Tm (- converts sentences into sequences of integers) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 311 Tm (- the same tokenizer is saved and reused during prediction) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 285 Tm (pad_sequences) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 256 Tm (Why it is used:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 230 Tm (- machine learning inputs should usually have the same length) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 204 Tm (How it works here:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 178 Tm (- shorter sequences are padded so all inputs have a consistent size) Tj ET
