stream
0 0 0 rg
BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 780 Tm (10. How Frontend And Backend Are Connected) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 747 Tm (The connection works like this:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 721 Tm (1. User types text in the frontend.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 703 Tm (2. JavaScript sends a POST request to `/api/predict`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 685 Tm (3. Flask receives the request.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 667 Tm (4. The backend predictor processes the text.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 649 Tm (5. Prediction results are returned as JSON.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 631 Tm (6. JavaScript receives the response.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 613 Tm (7. Suggestions are shown on the screen.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 587 Tm (This is the most important connection in the project.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 561 Tm (Example:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 535 Tm (- frontend sends: `{ "text": "machine learning", "top_n": 3 }`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 517 Tm (- backend returns: predicted next words with scores and source) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 491 Tm (11. How Backend And Model Are Connected) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 458 Tm (The backend does not train the model directly during user requests.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 432 Tm (Instead, it works like this:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 406 Tm (1. Training is done separately in `training/train_lstm.py`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 388 Tm (2. The trained model is saved in `artifacts/next_word_model.keras`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 370 Tm (3. The tokenizer is saved in `artifacts/tokenizer.pkl`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 352 Tm (4. Metadata is saved in `artifacts/metadata.json`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 334 Tm (5. Metrics are saved in `artifacts/metrics.json`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 316 Tm (6. The backend loads these files when starting or reloading.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 290 Tm (This separation is good because:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 264 Tm (- training is slow and should not happen during user requests) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 246 Tm (- prediction should be fast) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 228 Tm (- the architecture stays clean and modular) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 202 Tm (12. Why The Updated Training Pipeline Is Better) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 169 Tm (Problems in the original report code:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 143 Tm (- tokenizer saving logic was incorrect) Tj ET
